org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver

Interface DeleteTracker

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ScanDeleteTracker

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
public interface DeleteTracker
    This interface is used for the tracking and enforcement of Deletes during the course of a Get or Scan operation.

    This class is utilized through three methods:

    • add(byte[], int, int, long, byte) when encountering a Delete
    • isDeleted(byte[], int, int, long) when checking if a Put KeyValue has been deleted
    • update() when reaching the end of a StoreFile

       int qualifierOffset,

        Add the specified KeyValue to the list of deletes to check against for this row operation.

        This is called when a Delete is encountered in a StoreFile.

        Parameters:
        buffer - KeyValue buffer
        qualifierOffset - column qualifier offset
        qualifierLength - column qualifier length
        timestamp - timestamp
        type - delete type as byte

        boolean isEmpty()

      • update

        void update()
        Called at the end of every StoreFile.

        Many optimized implementations of Trackers will require an update at when the end of each StoreFile is reached.

      • reset
